<item>
            <title>[DERBY-74] SQLDecimal.getWholeDigits returns invalid result on JDK1.5.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-74</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With JDK1.5.0 the behaviour of BigDecimal.toString() has changed (thanks Sun) and for numbers &amp;lt; 1e-6 it now returns a String in exponential syntax. This causes the number of digits to be calculated incorrectly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a result, the ejbql test fails as the following snippet fails:&lt;br/&gt;
create table myDecimal (b DECIMAL(31,31))&lt;br/&gt;
insert into myDecimal VALUES(1e-30)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>JDK1.5.0</environment>
